	     <table class=mform  border=0 cellpadding=1 cellspacing=0 width=100%>
	     <form action=/cgi-bin/mrate.pl name=f10025507463371>
	     <tr><td id=headerrow colspan=2 class=mform valign=top><a name=classes.html?class=5&mid=10025507463371>&nbsp;</a><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=5&mid=10025507463371>RE: Solo</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=5&mid=10025507463371#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a>
	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Mon, Oct 8th 10:19 AM 2001</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=97237><span id= >Malace</span></a><br><span id=notbold>1 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [2.50]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Bards rock at solo if you know what you are doing.<br><br>They can:<br><br>Charm kite- agro 2 charm one and have it beat on the other till it dies then agro another and charm it to kill the half dead one and rinse and repeat.<br><br>Fear kite- Bards melee skills are low but this is still a very easy way to solo.&nbsp;&nbsp;Just have CHA up high and your brass skill up high even though you will not be using your instrument.<br><br>Dot kite- After Bards get all there dot songs they should have a magical drum of some sort.  This can take awhile but is very easy. All you do is twist 3 dots with Selo's and go to town staying out of range of the mob.<br><br>As for crappy heal songs... they aren't really heals.  They are regens and they are the best in the game.  As a level 51 Bard I can regen 39 hps a tick and this stacks with other classes regens as well to make it even higher.<br><br>All in All, Bards can solo very easily but it takes a long time.  The up side is there is little to no down time inbetween fights since we don't use mana and if you did your work right you wouldn't be hurt much.  I do agree Bards are best in a group but it is a nice option to solo too.<br><br>Oh by the way, I am playing a SK now and I am loving it!  Lots of fun, good solors too and can take a beating.<br><br>Malace<br>Minstrel<br><br>Darhan<br>Shadow Knight</p>&nbsp;<br> </td></td></tr>
