	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span><br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [2.50]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>First you need snare to fear-kite, so really Pali's can't fear-kite.&nbsp;&nbsp;Pali's solo using root, back off and heal, fight some more.<br><br>In Velius against the Cats, Wolves, Mamouths and all the other animals Rangers are great for soloing.  With snare, fear animals and root/dot for that last bit of life they solo faster than most.  Rangers also have track so they find the next kill faster than most.<br><br>Bards solo very well, but really, a Bard is best in a group.  Most groups will snatch up a bard if there is a slot open, so I see few ever soloing.  But they have snare and fear with ok damage so they can do it when they have too.<br><br>SK's have to be very selective on location and MOB to be able to solo.  Once you find a good fear track, and can consistantly pull the right level MOB SK's can solo very well.  The problem is the short duration of our snare (darkness line).  SK soloing takes alot of mana, so quite often you will be sitting medding to full between pulls, and will have to feign death with even high green adds.  Pets help if you have the right area to use them.<br><br>The best soloers are probably SK's and Rangers depending on the zone.</p>&nbsp;<br> </td></td></tr>
